title: Team Jets beat Premier League Three leaders Kent County
title_page: Team Jets beat Premier League Three leaders Kent County - BBC Sport
maintext:
Jersey's Team Jets netball team returned to winning ways in Premier League Three by beating leaders Kent County 46-38.
The Jets are the only team to have beaten Kent this season, having also recorded a 52-47 win over them at Les Ormes in October.
Jersey, who had lost their two previous matches, remain third in the table, eight points behind Kent.
They have four games left this season, with the final three all at home.
